parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, as well as create a distraction for the driver.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or impact
or deploy at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unavailability of airbag components can lead to delays in repairs, leaving vehicles without functioning airbags and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Difficulty in obtaining replacement airbag components
such as passenger-side airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can prevent the seat belt from functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle unlocks without warning
the seat belt locks in the retracted position
the seat belt does not come out of the holder
the seat belt will not buckle
the seat belt unwinds while buckled and will not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt locks up and will not release
the seat belt will not pull out easily
the seat belt tightens down on users while driving
the seat belt will not return to the retractor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A seat belt that is inoperative can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt is inoperative
the seat belt will not latch
the seat belt breaks free at the retractor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake module assembly can cause the ABS brake lights to illuminate, leading to reduced vehicle safety and potentially increased stopping distances.
symptoms: ABS brake lights illuminate
brake pedal locks up
extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to malfunction, leading to reduced braking performance and potentially increased stopping distances.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal does not engage when applying the brakes
brake pedal locks up.
